    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">So from this we see that if <em>ad</em>-<em>bc</em> is not 0 then our system of equations has a unique solution given by</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><em>x</em> = (<em>sd</em>-<em>bt</em>)/(<em>ad</em>-<em>bc</em>), <em>y</em>=(<em>at</em>-<em>sc</em>)/(<em>ad</em>-<em>bc</em>)</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Now you might assume all is good, we have analyzed our system, determined that our solutions fall into three different categories of no solution, infinite solutions and one unique solution, but there is still one thing left that you might have noticed. We have shown that a unique solution exists when ad-bc is not 0, but we have not shown that one doesn’t exist when <em>ad</em>-<em>bc</em> = 0. There could be some other method of solving our system that we are unaware of. To investigate this lets take a step back and draw a graph for an oblique line <em>ax</em> + <em>by</em> = <em>s </em>with the added restriction that both <em>a</em> and <em>b</em> are not equal to 0. An <strong>oblique</strong> line can described as a line that is neither horizontal or vertical.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
