    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">From this we can see the equation crosses the y-axis at the height <em>s</em>/<em>b</em> and the x-axis when <em>x</em> = <em>s</em>/<em>a</em> and <em>y</em> = 0.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">We can continue this process for different restrictions on <em>a</em>, <em>b</em>, and <em>s</em> to create a table describing the different <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Set_(mathematics)" target="_self">sets</a> of points.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
