    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Now we can think of the set of possible solutions for a given pair of linear equations. For example if we have an horizontal and vertical line there will be a single shared point. If we have a plane and any other type of linear equation we will get that type back. Continuing with this we will end up with the following table.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
